====Usage notes====
Often cited as the longest non-technical word in the English language, being one letter longer than the commonly cited [[antidisestablishmentarianism]]. In the debate on the remuneration of EU staff, Conservative MP {{w|Jacob Rees-Mogg}} used the word on 21st February 2012 making it the longest word ever used in the British House of Commons.

